# CRT scanline photon

**Where it lives**

- **Markup:** `_includes/layouts/base.njk` — `#crt-scanline-photons` (first child of `body`, `aria-hidden="true"`).
- **Styles:** `_includes/css/index.css` — `#crt-scanline-photons`, `.crt-photon`, `@keyframes crt-photon-ltr` / `crt-photon-rtl`. Uses the same radial **mask** as `body::before` so the sweep respects the vignette.
- **Behavior:** `_includes/js/scanline-photons.js` — random delay between bursts, one photon per burst, random row and L/R direction. Skips entirely when **`prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`**; CSS also hides `#crt-scanline-photons` in that case.

**Keep in sync**

- **`GRID_PX` (5)** in JS must match the **scanline repeat period** in `body::before`’s `repeating-linear-gradient` (currently **5px** per band cycle). If you change the gradient stripe height, update `GRID_PX` so photons sit on visible lines.

**Tuning**

- **Speed:** `--crt-photon-duration` on `#crt-scanline-photons .crt-photon` (not duplicated in JS).
- **Brightness / glow:** `.crt-photon` `background` and `box-shadow`; keyframe opacity plateaus (`0.88` in the `9%` / `91%` steps).
- **How often:** `MIN_GAP_MS` / `MAX_GAP_MS` in `scanline-photons.js`.

**User-facing docs:** `README.md` section “CRT scanline photon”.
